history.content:
I personally agree that you should probably Phase I EE128 (in the best interest of choosing a preferable lab) and phase II Math110, CS170. Speaking from personal experience, I was actually able to add CS170 during the adjustment period should I think Phase II should be okay for that.

Don't really know if 128 will be expanded but from my understanding, whatever is shown on the schedule of classes is all that the faculty knows about the course availability as well. If the class will be expanded, the faculty will immediately update it as well. 

Good luck!

I'm planning on taking CS170, EE128 (for which the lab section I need is already full), Math 110, and ENERES 190 (which is already on the waitlist). Which should I Phase I, besides Eneres 190? I'm thinking EE128. Also, Is there a high chance that 128 enrollment will be expanded?
